<p><b>What are definitional assertions?</b></p>

<p>Definitional assertions constrain the use and meaning of some sonstant. They are those GAFs (<a href="http://www.cyc.com/cycdoc/ref/glossary.html#GAF" target="reading_window">Ground Atomic Formulas</a>) which have a definitional predicate in their arg 0 slot.</p>

<p>
Definitional predicates are those predicates which are used to constrain other arguments. So, for example, the following are definitional predicates:</p>


<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cyc.com/cycdoc/vocab/fundamental-vocab.html#isa" target="reading_window">#$isa</a><tt></li>  
<li><a href="http://www.cyc.com/cycdoc/vocab/fundamental-vocab.html#genls" target="reading_window">#$genls</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cyc.com/cycdoc/vocab/fundamental-vocab.html#disjointWith" target="reading_window">#$disjointWith</a></li>
</ul>


<p>These predicates can be used to make the following definitional assertions about #$Animal:</p>

<ul>
<li>(#$isa #$Animal #$OrganismClassificationType)</li>
<li>(#$genls #$Animal #$Heterotroph)</li>
<li>(#$disjointWith #$Animal #$SomethingToWear)</li>
</ul>

